<item>
            <title>[OPENJPA-1237] WriteBehind configuration exception not thrown when it should be</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OPENJPA-1237</link>
                <project id="12310351" key="OPENJPA">OpenJPA</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;It seems like there should be exception(s) thrown when the new writebehind cache is not configured properly. For example, this is not a valid PU configuration since there is no DataCache specified. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &amp;lt;persistence-unit name=&quot;WriteBehind_JSE_INVALID_PU1&quot;&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
        &amp;lt;mapping-file&amp;gt;META-INF/orm.xml&amp;lt;/mapping-file&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
        &amp;lt;properties&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
            &amp;lt;property name=&quot;openjpa.DataCache&quot; value=&quot;false&quot;/&amp;gt;                                &lt;br/&gt;
            &amp;lt;property name=&quot;openjpa.WriteBehindCache&quot; value=&quot;true&quot;/&amp;gt;                         &lt;br/&gt;
            &amp;lt;property name=&quot;openjpa.WriteBehindCallback&quot; value=&quot;true(sleepTime=15000)&quot;/&amp;gt;     &lt;br/&gt;
        &amp;lt;/properties&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
    &amp;lt;/persistence-unit&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Yet there is no error or exception thrown when this statement is executed:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;           emf = Persistence.createEntityManagerFactory(&quot;WriteBehind_JSE_INVALID_PU1&quot;);&lt;/p&gt;</description>
